Spring Framework 4.3 (@GetMapping, @Post.evidence:
The `@GetMapping` and `@PostMapping` annotations were introduced in Spring Framework 4.3, released in June 2016. ([javadevjournal.com](https://javadevjournal.com/spring-mvc/spring-new-requestmapping-annotations/?utm_source=openai)) These annotations serve as shortcuts for `@RequestMapping` with specific HTTP methods, enhancing code readability and maintainability.

Prior to this, developers used `@RequestMapping` with the `method` attribute to specify HTTP methods:

```java
@RequestMapping(value = "/example", method = RequestMethod.GET)
public String handleGetRequest() {
    // handle GET request
}
```

With the introduction of `@GetMapping` and `@PostMapping`, the code becomes more concise:

```java
@GetMapping("/example")
public String handleGetRequest() {
    // handle GET request
}
```

This change aligns with the goal of making Spring MVC annotations more intuitive and easier to use. ([docs.spring.vmware.com](https://docs.spring.vmware.com/spring-framework/reference/web/webflux/controller/ann-requestmapping.html?utm_source=openai))

